<TITLE> 5 more BDR men give statements </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Apr 04 (bdnews24.com) - Five more BDR members gave 'confessional statements' Saturday in the BDR mutiny case. Chief metropolitan magistrates Julfiqar Hayat and Tofail Hasan recorded the statements of Nayek Sheikh Monirul Islam and sepoys Masud Ahmed, Jafar Ali, Jainul Abedin and Raihan Chowdhury from 3pm to 7pm. Sub-inspector Ekhlasur Rahman, at the CMM court's general recording office, told bdnews24.com 14 BDR members had given statements in the mutiny case to date. Meanwhile, metropolitan magistrate Abdul Majid granted seven days, instead of 10 days sought by CID, to grill 12 BDR members arrested anew. The accused were lance nayeks Hafez Ahmed, Mohammad Ismail and Masudur Rahman, sepoys Ekhlasur Rahman, Jasim Uddin, Julfiqar Hossain, Mizanur Rahman, Shah Alam, Abu Sadek and Masum Miah and signal men Noor Alam and Mizanur Rahman. b
